{
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONModel predictive control (MPC) has become one of the most prevalent strategies for managing large-scale and complex systems, primarily thanks to its predictive capabilities and explicit constraints handling [1].",
    "Data-based models such as neural networks (NNs) have recently gained popularity in the MPC community due to the vast availability of data and the relative ease of development in comparison to physicsbased models [2]- [4].",
    "However, when diverse datasets spanning different operating ranges are used, employing a single black-box model to represent significantly varying operating conditions often leads to degraded performance and loss of prediction accuracy [5], [6].A promising solution to this issue is ensemble learning [7], e.g., incremental learning [8] or a mixture of experts approach [9].",
    "These methods improve accuracy and generalization by training specialized models, or experts, on specific datasets corresponding to different operating domains, and subsequently combining their outputs [10].",
    "Several techniques have been proposed in the literature to combine the predictions of ensemble models."
  ]
}